* The cobra and bat fuzor let out a breath and shivered as the night air touched her armor, not even aware that two strange bots had just turned her over onto her back.
Her wings were all that was keeping her warm, now laying limp on the ground on either side of her.
Her own bat senses detected warmth near by, seemingly right beside her. But her body was to weak by damage and a bit of hunger to respond.
It also detected sone sort of sound, first high pitched ( the whistle ) and then scattered other vibrations that were of speech.
She shivered again as both her arms were taken hold of, her wings limp against her back as she was hauled upright.
The night air was full of chill but her shivers didn't get any worse, her senses alive but the body not able to repond.
The fuzor fembot slowly turned her head to the right and opened her optics the slightest crack, still not able to see before going unconsious.*
